<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1437,1557,1618]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1557,1582]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be easily distinguished from other Chinese 
<taxonomicName box="[1024,1142,1557,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chlamisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1024,1142,1557,1581]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Chlamisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by its purplish to reddish bronze coloration and the lacking of sutural teeth; its body size is smaller than most other congener species.
</paragraph>
